<h3>Improved Site Branding</h3>
<p>The Persona dialog can be customized with your site’s branding by specifying a site name, site logo, and now, <a href=\"http://identity.mozilla.com/post/55796551587/persona-a-login-that-matches-your-site\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Persona - A login that matches your site\">background color</a>. In addition, support for displaying your site’s terms of service and privacy policy have been added. Information on these options can be found on <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/navigator.id.request\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"MDN docs for navigator.id.request\">MDN</a>.</p>
<figure>
<img alt=\"Fully Branded Dialog\" src=\"http://shanetomlinson.com/static/images/rp-branding-persona-dialog.png\" /><p></p>
Persona dialog when opened from https://shanetomlinson.com<br />
</figure>
<h3>Elimination of comment spam</h3>
<p>With the “Enable for comments” option selected, the <a href=\"https://login.persona.org\" target=\"_blank\">Persona</a> plugin helps eliminate comment spam. A Persona account will be required to leave comments, a requirement that automated bots do not yet have. Until bot writers wisen up, Persona keeps spam at bay.</p>
<figure>
<img alt=\"Eliminate Comment Spam\" src=\"http://shanetomlinson.com/static/images/post-comment.png\" /><p></p>
Eliminate comment spam by selecting “Enable for Comments”<br />
</figure>
