<p>This shows accessing the fields from the <code>ScriptView</code> view of the <code>Node</code> then switching to the <code>LayoutView</code> to get access to the <code>layout_data</code>. Trying to modify the non-layout fields with the <code>LayoutView</code> should fail. Build the example with <code>rustc main.rc</code> and make sure <code>main.rc</code> and <code>layout.rs</code> are in the current directory.</p>
<p>The Servo code is quite a bit more complex than this but hopefully it helps with understanding the idiom of phantom type usage in nodes. If I’ve made any mistakes in my understanding of how things work, please let me know!</p>
