<ul>
<li><strong>Meeting up</strong> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geocaching\">geocaching</a> with <a href=\"http://twiter.com/lordlangley73\">James Langley</a> while talking <a href=\"http://openbadges.org\">Open Badges</a>. He was up near where I live in Northumberland preparing for an activity day. <img alt=\":-)\" class=\"wp-smiley\" src=\"http://dougbelshaw.com/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\" /> </li>
<li><strong>Wondering</strong> <a href=\"http://dougbelshaw.com/blog/2013/06/29/why-would-i-send-my-child-to-secondary-school/\">why I’d send my children to secondary school</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Booking</strong> travel. Lots of travel.</li>
<li><strong>Celebrating</strong> my <a href=\"http://dougbelshaw.com/blog/2013/07/01/a-quick-look-back-at-my-first-year-at-mozilla/\">first year at Mozilla</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Hosting</strong> the weekly <a href=\"http://mzl.la/weblitstd\">Web Literacy Standard</a> community call. You can listen again <a href=\"http://weblitstd.tumblr.com/post/54420109502/weekly-community-call-1st-july-2013-in-this\">here</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Communicating</strong> with various people and organizations via Skype/phone/email about integrating with the Open Badges Infrastructure (OBI) – including <a href=\"http://codecademy.com/\">Codecademy</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Releasing</strong> v0.7 of my iterative ebook: <a href=\"http://dougbelshaw.com/ebooks/digilit\"><em>The Essential Elements of Digital Literacies</em></a></li>
<li><strong>Talking</strong> with <a href=\"http://twitter.com/epilepticrabbit\">Laura Hilliger</a> about the link between <a href=\"http://hivenyc.org/kits.html\">hacktivity kits</a> and the Web Literacy Standard.</li>
<li><strong>Mapping</strong> the UK Open Badges people/organizations/projects I’ve spoken to who are ready to issue badges.</li>
<li><strong>Planning</strong> a potential <a href=\"https://gameon.mozilla.org/en-US/\">Game On</a>-style challenge or competition for aligning with the Web Literacy Standard with <a href=\"http://twitter.com/varelidi\">Chloe Varelidi</a>. She also pointed me towards <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/demos/devderby\">MDN’s Dev Derby</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Talking</strong> to the Comms team about what we need to do in the run up to the beta launch of the Web Literacy Standard on July 26th.</li>
