<p>So which industry has large and fairly constant power costs it would like to reduce by buying some of that power at off-peak prices, equipment which can be placed anywhere, including where land prices are cheap, plus a lot of waste heat it doesn’t know what to do with?</p>
<p>Someone should come up with a gas compression power storage system for data centres.</p>
<p>Cost of power, ballpark: $0.06 per kWH peak (say 8am – 6pm), $0.03 off-peak<br />
Power consumption of server: 1KW<br />
