Potential saving per server per year if all power used were priced at the off-peak price: $110</p>
<p>One issue is that a 5l bottle <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Compressed_air_storage#Energy_density_and_efficiency\">can store</a> 500kJ of energy (0.14 kwH), so you’d need 500l per server. That’s a lot, so you may not be able to get the full saving unless you use an underground cavern rather than surface storage tanks. But if land is cheap, you could make a dent in your power bill.</p>
