<p>Finally, I have found the solution with very kind help of Peter Hutterer  and his blogpost on <a href=\"http://who-t.blogspot.com.au/2011/03/custom-input-device-configuration-in.html\">Custom input device configuration in GNOME</a>. When the example script from <code>gnome-settings-daemon</code> is modified to include the configuration, it could also set Yubikey (and only Yubikey) input device to us keyboard layout. The key part is:</p>
